sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(request_id) AS total_requests
FROM size_conversion_requests
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT COUNT(request_id) AS active_requests_count
FROM size_conversion_requests
WHERE is_active = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "More than 10 models" implies a significant product range;
- "More than 5 active size conversions" suggests active engagement with size variations;
- "More than 2 reports generated by users" indicates user interaction and possibly high user interest or activity.

- "First model in the alphabetical order" means the model with the smallest alphabetical name within each brand;
- "Most lucrative" refers to the models that generate the highest revenue;
- "Top 10" means the results are limited to the 10 models with the highest revenue.

- "Prolific report generators" refers to users who have generated the highest number of reports;
- "Realm of size conversion requests" indicates that the reports are related to size conversion activities;
- "Productivity" is measured by the number of reports generated.

sql:
SELECT source_size, target_size
FROM size_conversion_requests
WHERE status = 'completed';

external_knowledge:
- "Spring of 2023" refers to the period starting from April 1, 2023;
- "Engagement" is measured by the number of system accesses;
- "Active users" are those who are currently active in the system.

- 'First standard' refers to the size standard with ID 1;
- 'Second standard' refers to the size standard with ID 2;
- 'Successfully converted' means the conversion request status is 'completed'.

- 'Men's shoe models' refers to shoe models designed for men;
- 'Currently active' means the conversion is marked as active in the database;
- 'General average' is the average heel to toe length across all active conversions.
